Note that by definition of [[Definition:Inverse Completion|inverse completion]], $\left({T, \circ'}\right)$ is a [[Definition:Semigroup|semigroup]].\nThus $\circ'$ is [[Definition:Associative Operation|associative]].\nFirst it is demonstrated that $S \circ' C^{-1}$ is a [[Definition:Semigroup|semigroup]].\nLet $x, z \in S$.\nLet $y, w \in C$.\nThen: 
