It is proved that $\struct {C, \circ}$ is a [[Definition:Subsemigroup|subsemigroup]] of $\struct {S, \circ}$ by [[Cancellable Elements of Semigroup form Subsemigroup]].\n=== Proof of at most one such homomorphism ===\nTo show there is at most one such [[Definition:Homomorphism (Abstract Algebra)|homomorphism]]:\nLet $\psi$ be a [[Definition:Homomorphism (Abstract Algebra)|homomorphism]] from $\struct {S', \circ'}$ into $\struct {T, *}$ [[Definition:Extension of Mapping|extending]] $\phi$.\nIt will be shown that for each [[Definition:Element|element]] in the [[Definition:Domain of Mapping|domain]] of $\psi$ , its [[Definition:Image of Element under Mapping|image]] is uniquely determined by $\phi$.\nIt will therefore follow that $\psi$ is the only such [[Definition:Extension of Mapping|extension]] of $\phi$.\nNow $\map \phi y$ is [[Definition:Invertible Element|invertible]] and hence [[Definition:Cancellable Element|cancellable]] for $*$ by [[Invertible Element of Monoid is Cancellable]].\nAs $\psi$ is an [[Definition:Extension of Mapping|extension]] of $\phi$, it follows that $\map \psi y$ is also [[Definition:Cancellable Element|cancellable]] for $*$.\nConsider: 
 :$\map \psi {x \circ' y^{-1} } * \map \psi y$ 
